This keeps confusing me.
If you put html tags in the body of a macro in wiki markup, and the macro *doesn't exist*, then the html will be displayed in the rich text editor, and lost when you save, or go back to wiki markup.  The most likely reason this would be a problem is if somebody edits a page with an html macro on it, while that macro is temporarily disabled.

For me it just keeps tricking me when I test that escaping in the HTML macro works.

To reproduce.
# Insert the following wiki markup into the wiki editor (without the noformat)
{noformat}
{macrodoesnotexist}
Blah <b>bold</b> blah
{macrodoesnotexist}
{noformat}
# Switch to the RTE.  bold will be in *bold*.
# Switch back to Wiki markup.  The b tags will be gone.

